&lt;p&gt;SPECIALITY DOCTOR IN SEXUAL HEALTH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit a Speciality Doctor in Sexual Health to join our team at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals. This is a full time post to provide input within the Sexual Health service for Sheffield based at the Royal Hallamshire Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is envisaged that the post holder will undertake STI clinics and develop a special interest in contraception or HIV. The post holder will support and develop the Sexual Health Service in Sheffield. The post holder will share clinical responsibilities with professional colleagues and will actively contribute to the governance arrangements of the department. The post holder will be encouraged to contribute to research and training activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee will be expected to take part in undergraduate and postgraduate teaching and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have full GMC registration and relevant post graduate experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from those unable, for personal reasons, to work on a whole time basis or a job share basis will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non-UK/EEA applicants should ensure they are aware of the recent changes to the Immigration rules. For further information on how this may affect your application visit the UK Government website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
